\chapter*{Dalesmen}

\section*{Resources}

Fertile lands, good clays, coal and oil. Copper, Iron.
Aliantha plants.

\section*{Technology}
\section*{Magic}

\section*{Subsistence Patterns}

Grain and fruit growing as well as trade.

\section*{Values and Kinship}

Patriarchal with a strong male rule. They value practicality,
thrift and caution.

\section*{Language}

A very broadly spoken slow and low tongue similiar to welsh.

All males are taught to read to rank 4 or more. No woman is taught to
read beyond rank 3.

They share a written runic form with the Vairmen.

H\={o}tman  means Headman.


\section*{Religion,Myths,and History}

Like many of the cultures of the region the men of the dale worship
the Lord and the Lady. The dalesmen view the Lord as the master and the Lady
as the subservient adjunct to the Lord.

The Lord appears as a tall bald man with a hammer and an Axe in hand.

\section*{Tradition}

The bride generally marries into an already established family and becomes
the ``Least Wife''. She is called this until a newer wife comes into the
family.

Heavy incest taboos, no particular age taboos. It is a punishable offence
if a woman expresses interest in a man. As a esult of their culture there
are a large number of lesbian relationships.

There are many traditions regarding the planting of crops and such.

